{"cursor":"38128","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Perspective' (from Latin perspicere, to see through) in the graphic arts, such\nas drawing, is an approximate representation, on a flat surface (such as paper),\nof an image as it is seen by the eye. The two most characteristic features of\nperspective are that objects are drawn:\n\n* Smaller as their distance from the observer increases\n* Foreshortened: the size of an object's dimensions along the line of sight are\n  relatively shorter than dimensions across the line of sight\n","linknr":516,"url":"Perspective_(graphical)","recorded":1362893267,"links":46,"instances":["an","moon","visual","football","heraldry","florence","visual_arts","graphics","geometry"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Perspective projection","Technical drawing","Functions and mappings","Composition in visual art"],"headings":["Overview","History","Types of perspective","Methods of construction","Example","Limitations","See also","Notes","References","Further reading","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Staircase_perspective.jpg/280px-Staircase_perspective.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Axonometric_projection.svg/150px-Axonometric_projection.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/93/Perspectiva-1.svg/210px-Perspectiva-1.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d2/Perspectiva-2.svg/210px-Perspectiva-2.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Reconstruction_of_the_temple_of_Jerusalem.jpg/300px-Reconstruction_of_the_temple_of_Jerusalem.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/StPaul%27sCros